description: From Anglo-Norman supposaille, supposail, corresponding to suppose +‎ -al.

entries.meaning: The act of supposing; supposition. [from 15th c.]
Something supposed; a supposition, a hypothesis. [from 16th c.]
examples: [W]e may, if we attentively consider and examine it, find that there are circumstances sufficient, upon the supposals of the excellent contrivance of their machine, to excite and force them to act after such or such a manner […].
